A SIGORA INITIATIVE

We formed Sigora Haiti as a business model with a vision.
What began as a dream to bring electricity to a clinic in Môle St. Nicholas has evolved into a full-scale green utility project.  With community support and working with a team of investors, Sigora Haiti is developing the necessary infrastructure to generate and distribute wind and solar power to the people of Haiti–power that is clean, reliable, and affordable.  Our goal is to generate 116,000kW of power for nearly 2 million people and create 5,800 jobs in the process by the year 2025.

