                There are 1.3 billion people without power. The International Energy Agency estimates that
40% are potential customers for microutilities. That is a huge market opportunity with tremendous poverty reduction potential.  We want to capitalize on that. 

Sigora International is a specialty provider of microutility energy systems designed for frontier markets. A unique approach for the environmentally and financially sustainable electrification of underserved communities, Sigora deploys specialized hardware, web-managed software, and simple pre-payment solutions specifically designed for emergent energy markets. Sigora can power anything from a small fishing village to a large city, all with the same technology, sustainably. 

Our mission is to power and empower the world with clean, reliable, and fairly-priced energy using a commercially viable microutility model that can be brought to scale faster, cheaper, and more effectively than existing electrification solutions.

Our aim is to p...
            

                There are 1.3 billion people without power. The International Energy Agency estimates that
40% are potential customers for microutilities. That is a huge market opportunity with tremendous poverty reduction potential.  We want to capitalize on that. 

Sigora International is a specialty provider of microutility energy systems designed for frontier markets. A unique approach for the environmentally and financially sustainable electrification of underserved communities, Sigora deploys specialized hardware, web-managed software, and simple pre-payment solutions specifically designed for emergent energy markets. Sigora can power anything from a small fishing village to a large city, all with the same technology, sustainably. 

Our mission is to power and empower the world with clean, reliable, and fairly-priced energy using a commercially viable microutility model that can be brought to scale faster, cheaper, and more effectively than existing electrification solutions.

Our aim is to provide underserved populations with a first rate electric utility service that is tailored to their needs, facilitates connectivity, accommodates a dynamic energy landscape, and provides a return on investment. 

Sigora’s grid technology is designed to provide more than just power metering and production monitoring, it is an integrated micro-utility management system. The proprietary smart meter and cloud-based API software automate account management tasks, monitor the technical and financial performance of the grid, and provide real-time data analytics and meter control, enabling Sigora to troubleshoot and address problems before they become serious. 

Because Sigora’s meters communicate using mesh networks it is simple to implement a captive portal for internet access. When enabled, every meter in a grid becomes part of a large wireless network and provides internet access to the local community.

The modular design of the system supplies a range of power to meet the dynamic energy needs of an energy emerging market. Unlike other decentralized energy-access solutions like standalone microgrids and solar home kits, the single, split and tri-phase configurations of Sigora’s meters enable the system to power anything from a small fishing village to a large city.            
